17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
19 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 335 of Title 61, unless there is
20 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
21 A. Any person may forage for nuts and edible plants or fungi on
22 state-owned or state-managed property accessible to the public for
23 personal consumption only except when such nuts and other edible
24 plants or fungi are:
Req. No. 13566 Page 1

1 1. From crops certified by the Oklahoma Agricultural Experiment
2 Station system or the Oklahoma Cooperative Extension Service of the
3 Oklahoma State University Division of Agricultural Sciences and
4 Natural Resources, as provided in Section 8-33 of Title 2 of the
5 Oklahoma Statutes; or
6 2. From plants that are threatened or endangered.
7 B. Any person foraging pursuant to this section is encouraged
8 to:
9 1. Wear an outer garment of hunter orange that is clearly
10 visible while in the field; and
11 2. Recognize which nuts and edible plants or fungi are safe for
12 human consumption.
13 C. As used in this section:
14 1. “State-owned or state-managed property accessible to the
15 public” means property owned or managed by an agency, municipality,
16 or political subdivision of this state designated for public use,
17 unless the property is located on:
18 a. state-owned or university-owned test or research
19 farms,
20 b. land leased to an individual or entity pursuant to
21 Section 1056 of Title 64 of the Oklahoma Statutes, who
22 has not given permission to an individual to forage,
23 or
24
Req. No. 13566 Page 2

1 c. property otherwise restricted for public access by
2 state or federal law including, but not limited to:
3 (1) land along public roads, highways, turnpikes, and
4 interstates,
5 (2) areas owned or operated by a law enforcement
6 agency or used for law enforcement training, or
7 (3) areas surrounding correction facilities owned or
8 operated by the Department of Corrections, a
9 county, a municipality, or a private entity
10 contracted by the Department of Corrections to
11 operate in this state;
12 2. “Edible plant or fungi” means a plant or fungi commonly
13 found in the wild, which is edible to humans in part or in its
14 entirety and may require cooking to make safe for consumption;
15 3. “Nut” means a dry fruit that has a single seed, a hard
16 shell, and a protective husk; and
17 4. "Personal consumption" means an amount that can be consumed
18 in a few days by a person and not sold to another person.
19 D. 1. After July 1, 2026, any person who is lawfully on a
20 Wildlife Management Area owned or managed by the Department of
21 Wildlife Conservation may forage along with other permitted
22 activities as authorized by the Oklahoma Wildlife Conservation
23 Commission.
24
